OL,3,CMan says his twin's killers deserve a
OL,4,Csecond chance
OL,6,F"Forgiveness is a personal journey
OL,7,Fthat we go on, my definition is that
OL,8,FI'm forgiving the crime, I'm accepting
OL,9,Fof their freedom, I'm accepting and
OL,10,Funderstanding of what happened to
OL,11,FSimon and I'm able to live at peace
OL,12,Fwith that and I try not to be angry
OL,13,Fabout it.
OL,15,F"But I'm not yet ready to say 'I
OL,16,Fforgive you Craig, I forgive you Carl'
OL,17,Fand shake their hand.
OL,19,F"I'm not in that position, but I'm not
OL,20,Fclosing the door on that. Maybe it's
OL,21,Fpart of my life journey."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
